dder/2001/01/09/krtbn/0000-0424-PO-UTILITY

UTILITIES AND ENERGY COMPANIES TURN TO EXCHANGES -- NEW ENERGY MARKETPLACES 
SEEK TO DRIVE EFFICIENCIES IN HOPES OF LOWERING COSTS
Heating oil shortages in the Northeast, potential electrical brownouts in 
California, and high gasoline prices nationwide are front-page news these 
days.
